On Thu, 7 Aug 2003, Acoustic Canada wrote:

> It appears to me that the thermostat is not opening the cooling flaps in my
> 75 FI westy (Cable is frayed and I  am not seeing any movement)  - not
> having a spare and finding that I am getting temps of 250 driving around
> town what can I do in the short tern until I can replace - Is it safe to
> unclip the spring and wire them open - I assume that pushing the control arm
> down opens the flaps

no the spring opens the flaps, so if the cable fails it fails in the
coolest position, so you can remove the cable and allow the spring to pull
it to the full open position.

